SPECIES. — 
<taxonomicName id="22D00CEDFF9CAE34FEB0FC96FDDCC424" authority="Spengler, 1799" authorityName="Spengler" authorityYear="1799" box="[282,613,844,868]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis id="D7A4AB7CFF9CAE34FEB0FC96FE77C424" box="[282,462,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Scyllarus guineensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="81410A9FFF9CAE34FE78FC96FDDCC424" author="SPENGLER L." box="[466,613,844,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" pagination="333 - 340" refId="ref13391" refString="SPENGLER L. 1799. - Beskrivelse af en nye Art Kraebs, Scyllarus Guineensis. Det Kongelige Danske Videnskabers-Selskab Skrivter (2) 5: 333 - 340, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1799">Spengler, 1799</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ADCA24E5FF9CAE34FFDBFC57FCD1C4C4" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FFDBFC57FBDFC6CE" blockId="1.[112,648,805,1224]" lastBlockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">DIAGNOSIS. — Carapace rather high, not depressed, quadrangular in outline, slightly longer than wide. Upper surface rough, with tubercles. Cervical, postcervical and branchiocardiac grooves, not very deep. Marginal groove distinct; with shallow cervical, but no postcervical incision on lateral margin which bears several teeth. Orbits on anterior margin of carapace close to anterolateral angles; distance between orbit and anterolateral angle less than 1/10 of distance between orbits, latter widely open anteriorly; intercalated plate poorly developed. Antenna not forming part of orbit. Upper surface of carapace without distinct carinae, with several teeth present. Rostral, pregastric and gastric teeth in median line; two submedian cardiac teeth on cardiac elevation; two teeth on branchial region behind cervical groove; and distinct postorbital tooth. No posteromedian tooth. Entire surface of carapace covered with small squamiform tubercles surrounded by short bristle-like hairs, some tubercles larger, even becoming tooth-shaped.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FE4AFCC0C56C" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">
First abdominal somite with deep uninterrupted transverse groove filled with hairs. Following somites with anterior half smooth and posterior part with complex sculpturation resembling that of 
<taxonomicName id="22D00CEDFF9CAE34FB8FFE3AFCF7C552" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="D7A4AB7CFF9CAE34FB8FFE3AFB00C6B8" box="[1061,1209,480,504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Scyllarus arctus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
, but with grooves wider and sculpted figures more elevated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FDF5FC98C521" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Calcified part of telson with tooth on each posterolateral angle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FDBEFCD3C5F1" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Distal part of antennular somite rather long, ending in two teeth placed close together at either side of median incision of segment.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FD69FCDDC440" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Ultimate segment of antenna with many large and small teeth. Fourth segment with strong teeth on anterior and lateral margins.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FCD9FB00C45B" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" box="[699,1209,771,795]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">
Epistome, mouthparts and branchiae as in 
<taxonomicName id="22D00CEDFF9CAE34FBFFFCD9FB0AC45B" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1898" box="[1109,1203,771,795]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7A4AB7CFF9CAE34FBFFFCD9FB0AC45B" box="[1109,1203,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Scyllarides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FCC7FCFBC42A" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Pereiopods with first leg stronger than following ones. Dactyli naked, not flattened above. Fifth leg of female ending in chela.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FCB6FCD1C4C4" blockId="1.[675,1212,215,900]" box="[699,872,876,900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Pleopods normal.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ADCA24E5FF9CAE34FD0FFC6BFBCBC388" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD0FFC6BFCB0C489" blockId="1.[677,1210,945,1224]" box="[677,777,945,971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD0FFC0AFC1AC36A" blockId="1.[677,1210,945,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">
The genus contains three species, of which the oldest, 
<taxonomicName id="22D00CEDFF9CAE34FD65FC2AFBF8C34A" authority="Spengler, 1799" authorityName="Spengler" authorityYear="1799" box="[719,1089,1008,1034]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis id="D7A4AB7CFF9CAE34FD65FC2AFC2FC34A" box="[719,918,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Scyllarus guineensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="81410A9FFF9CAE34FC37FC2AFBF8C34A" author="SPENGLER L." box="[925,1089,1008,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" pagination="333 - 340" refId="ref13391" refString="SPENGLER L. 1799. - Beskrivelse af en nye Art Kraebs, Scyllarus Guineensis. Det Kongelige Danske Videnskabers-Selskab Skrivter (2) 5: 333 - 340, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1799">Spengler, 1799</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is the 
<typeStatus id="3A6BC9CCFF9CAE34FB21FC2AFB00C34A" box="[1163,1209,1008,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">type</typeStatus>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E56F776EFF9CAE34FD11FBF5FBCBC388" blockId="1.[677,1210,945,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">
Formerly the species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="22D00CEDFF9CAE34FB85FBF5FB39C309" authorityName="Holthuis" authorityYear="1960" box="[1071,1152,1071,1097]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Arctides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7A4AB7CFF9CAE34FB85FBF5FB39C309" box="[1071,1152,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Arctides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="22D00CEDFF9CAE34FC89FB95FC37C329" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1898" box="[803,910,1103,1129]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7A4AB7CFF9CAE34FC89FB95FC37C329" box="[803,910,1103,1129]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="418">Scyllarides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they differ in so many points that it proved necessary to erect a separate genus for them. The three species may be distinguished with the help of the following key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
